From 83ba5bbbd171a23d4ce3a73998a15e845b80f938 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Nikolas Pertschy <nikolas.pertschy@dataciders.com>
Date: Wed, 27 May 2026 11:27:34 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 1/2] feat(copilot): add GitHub Enterprise support

Allow the Copilot adapter to authenticate against a GitHub Enterprise
instance by setting `github_enterprise_url` in the adapter's `env`
table. Falls back to the `GH_HOST` environment variable, then
`github.com`.

- Add `resolve_endpoints()` to token module, returning the correct
  token, auth hostname, and stats endpoints for both public GitHub
  and GHE instances
- Pass the adapter through all `token.fetch()` / `token.init()` call
  sites so endpoint resolution has access to the configured host
- Fix `handlers()` in the adapter to derive the base URL dynamically
  rather than hardcoding `api.githubcopilot.com`, so GHE-issued
  endpoint URLs are preserved across chat/completions and responses
  endpoint switches
- Fix `stats.lua` to use the stats endpoint (3rd return value of
  `resolve_endpoints`) instead of the token endpoint
- Invalidate the module-level OAuth/Copilot token cache when the
  target host changes, preventing a cached public-GitHub token from
  being reused for GHE requests and vice versa
- Add six tests covering `resolve_endpoints` URL construction,
  protocol stripping, `GH_HOST` fallback, and cache invalidation
- Document the `github_enterprise_url` option in adapters-http.md
